<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="29" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="29">
The species was formally attributed tothe genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holynski" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Bilyaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Bilyaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B12" refString="Bily, S, 2004. Taxonomic studies on Anthaxiina Gory &amp; Laporte de Castelnau and Curina Holynski (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). Zootaxa 555: 1 - 11" title="Taxonomic studies on Anthaxiina Gory &amp; Laporte de Castelnau and Curina Holynski (Coleoptera: Buprestidae)." volume="555" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bílý">Bily</normalizedToken>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
. Already in the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos, A" journalOrPublisher="Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria)" pageId="28" pageNumber="45" pagination="5 - 235" refId="B21" refString="Cobos, A, 1972. Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Tercera parte: Subgenero Agrilaxia Kerremans. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria) 16: 5 - 235" title="Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Tercera parte: Subgenero Agrilaxia Kerremans." volume="16" year="1972">Cobos, 1972</bibRefCitation>
) noted that this species is an extraordinary and isolated element of the Neotropical 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" rank="tribe" tribe="Anthaxiini">Anthaxiini</taxonomicName>
being very similar to the European species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1803" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funerula" subGenus="Anthaxia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Anthaxia (Anthaxia) funerula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Illiger, 1803 species-group. After having studied the holotype and further, male specimen of this species from NMPC I found that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Bílý" baseAuthorityYear="2013" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="willineri" subGenus="Bilyaxia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Anthaxia (Bilyaxia) willineri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ought to be removed from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Holynski" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Bilyaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Bilyaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and a new genus should be proposed for this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="29">I failed to find any difference between the sexes and also no significant variability since only two specimens were available for study.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Length: 4.2-4.4 mm; width: 1.4-1.5 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
